a:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Autonomous solar farm builder exits field testing"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"AI-driven construction claims 2x speed over humans"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Hardware limits: terrain, payload, and maintenance reality"}]]}]]}]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["The US solar industry needs to move faster—",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.eia.gov/electricity/monthly/epm_table_grapher.php?t=epmt_6_07_b","children":"1.4 GW of new capacity"}]," must come online ",["$","em",null,{"children":"monthly"}]," to meet 2035 decarbonization targets. Enter ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Terafab V2"}],", Berkeley-based ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://terabase.energy/","children":"Terabase Energy"}],"’s automated solar farm constructor, now exiting field tests and shipping commercially. The pitch is straightforward: autonomous robots and AI replace slow, labor-intensive panel mounting, promising ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"2x faster deployment"}]," in ideal conditions.\nBut here’s the catch: ",["$","em",null,{"children":"ideal conditions"}]," rarely exist. The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=example","children":"demo videos"}]," show Terafab’s articulated arms placing panels with millimeter precision on flat, obstacle-free terrain. Real solar farms? Think ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"uneven grading, wind gusts, and mud after rain"}],"—the kind of variables that turn ‘autonomous’ into ‘remote-supervised’ faster than a marketing deck can say ",["$","em",null,{"children":"scalable"}],".\nTerabase isn’t wrong about the need. Solar installations ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.seia.org/solar-industry-research-data","children":"account for 53% of new US electric capacity"}]," in 2024, but labor shortages and permitting delays strangle growth. A robot that ",["$","em",null,{"children":"actually"}]," works could unclog the bottleneck. The question isn’t whether Terafab V2 is impressive—it’s whether it’s ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"deployment-ready"}]," or just another polished demo waiting for reality to intrude."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/solar-farm-robots-can-they-survive-outside-the-dem/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Od labsa do prakse: Terafab V2 obećava brže gradnje, ali stvari postaju zanimljive kad padne kiša.","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"Od labsa do prakse: Terafab V2 obećava brže gradnje, ali stvari postaju zanimljive kad padne kiša."}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Let’s talk hardware. Terafab V2’s specs—",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://terabase.energy/terafab","children":"payload capacity"}],", battery life, and terrain tolerance—aren’t public, but industry chatter suggests ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"payload limits under 100 kg per arm"}]," and ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"operational windows constrained by weather"}],". That’s fine for lightweight panels but problematic for ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"racking systems or heavy-duty mounts"}]," required in high-wind zones. Then there’s maintenance: autonomous or not, ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S095741742030456X","children":"dust accumulation on sensors"}]," and mechanical wear in 24/7 operation demand ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"human oversight"}],"—the kind Terabase’s marketing glosses over.\nThe real test isn’t whether Terafab V2 ",["$","em",null,{"children":"can"}]," build a solar farm—it’s whether it can do so ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"cheaper and more reliably than humans"}]," at scale. Early adopters like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.nexteraenergy.com/","children":"NextEra Energy"}]," are watching, but mass deployment hinges on ","$L13",": certification for varied terrains, proof of long-term reliability, and a total cost of ownership that beats manual labor. Right now, Terabase is selling a ","$L14",", not a turnkey solution.\nAnd then there’s the elephant in the room: ","$L15",". Permitting, grid interconnection, and supply chain snags dwarf the time saved by faster panel placement. Terafab V2 might shave weeks off a 6-month project—but if the grid connection is backlogged for a year, does it matter?"]}]]}]
